Towers of Hanoi
===============
(c) Paul Griffiths 1999
Email: mail@paulgriffiths.net


Function
========

Outputs the moves necessary to solve the "Towers of Hanoi" puzzle.


Usage
=====

    hanoi -d{n} -s{n} -e{n}

where:

    -d{n} : specifies the number of disks to move
    -s{n} : specifies the column to move them from (1, 2 or 3)
    -e{n} : specifies the column to move them to (1, 2 or 3)


Installation
============

If your system supports "make", simply type:

    make

at the command line. Otherwise, compile "hanoi.c" in your usual way.


